ic.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132260665,imgsize-86396.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Is Connor Murphy dead or alive? What we know about the viral rumor surrounding the YouTube bodybuilder]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132250995.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Connor Murphy’s reported death remains an unconfirmed rumor as of July 2026. Claims circulating online largely stem from social media posts and statements that have not been independently verified. No family member, representative, or authority has confirmed his death. Murphy rose to fame through fitness and bodybuilding content, and questions about his current status remain unanswered pending official information.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/is-connor-murphy-dead-or-alive-what-we-know-about-the-viral-rumor-surrounding-the-youtube-bodybuilder/articleshow/132250995.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/is-connor-murphy-dead-or-alive-what-we-know-about-the-viral-rumor-surrounding-the-youtube-bodybuilder/articleshow/132250995.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T05:21:38+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132250993,imgsize-860227.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kudzu was planted across the US South in the 1930s to fight soil erosion, but later it became the vine that 'ate the South' sprawling across roadsides and abandoned land]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132259696.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/kudzu-was-planted-across-the-us-south-in-the-1930s-to-fight-soil-erosion-but-later-it-became-the-vine-that-ate-the-south-sprawling-across-roadsides-and-abandoned-land/articleshow/132259696.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/kudzu-was-planted-across-the-us-south-in-the-1930s-to-fight-soil-erosion-but-later-it-became-the-vine-that-ate-the-south-sprawling-across-roadsides-and-abandoned-land/articleshow/132259696.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T15:56:40+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132260571,imgsize-1664798.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Not important for Denmark': Trump says US needs Greenland for 'protection of the world']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132259624.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[President Trump again urged the United States to control Greenland. He stated the Arctic island is vital for global security. Denmark's Prime Minister Mette Frederiksen rejected the demand, calling Greenland not for sale. Greenland's leadership also opposes any US acquisition of the territory. This ongoing dispute strains relations between the United States and Denmark.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/not-important-for-denmark-trump-says-us-needs-greenland-for-protection-of-the-world/articleshow/132259624.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/not-important-for-denmark-trump-says-us-needs-greenland-for-protection-of-the-world/articleshow/132259624.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T15:24:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132259783,imgsize-91250.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[US charges puts gangsters Lawrence Bishnoi and Goldy Brar at centre of transnational murder, stops short of accusing India]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132258677.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-charges-puts-gangsters-lawrence-bishnoi-and-goldy-brar-at-centre-of-transnational-murder-stops-short-of-accusing-india/articleshow/132258677.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-charges-puts-gangsters-lawrence-bishnoi-and-goldy-brar-at-centre-of-transnational-murder-stops-short-of-accusing-india/articleshow/132258677.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T14:38:16+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Chidanand Rajghatta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132259074,imgsize-96924.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft's $7.3 billion AI data centre has been sued by neighbours sick of noise that never stops, doesn’t let them sleep]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132257306.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Microsoft's latest AI data center in Wisconsin is under fire as residents file a lawsuit claiming the relentless noise from generators and HVAC systems is harming their property. While Microsoft asserts its dedication to being a good neighbor and has taken steps to mitigate noise, the local community remains unimpressed, especially with more data centers on the horizon that may escalate tensions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/microsofts-7-3-billion-ai-data-centre-has-been-sued-by-neighbours-sick-of-noise-that-never-stops-doesnt-let-them-sleep/articleshow/132257306.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/microsofts-7-3-billion-ai-data-centre-has-been-sued-by-neighbours-sick-of-noise-that-never-stops-doesnt-let-them-sleep/articleshow/132257306.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T15:04:56+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI News Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132257517,imgsize-325800.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Egypt has uncovered a well-preserved 1,600-year-old Byzantine-era city in Dakhla Oasis: Homes, basilica church, ovens, coins and writing fragments show how people lived in the western desert]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132257013.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Egypt has unveiled remarkable archaeological discoveries that shed light on its rich historical heritage. Among these is a remarkably preserved Byzantine-era city located in the western desert, which reveals fascinating details about urban life and development during that time. Additionally, the recent unearthing of eighteen ancient tombs near Alexandria enhances the region's archaeological narrative, aiming to invigorate Egypt's crucial tourism industry.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/egypt-has-uncovered-a-well-preserved-1600-year-old-byzantine-era-city-in-dakhla-oasis-homes-basilica-church-ovens-coins-and-writing-fragments-show-how-people-lived-in-the-western-desert/articleshow/132257013.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/egypt-has-uncovered-a-well-preserved-1600-year-old-byzantine-era-city-in-dakhla-oasis-homes-basilica-church-ovens-coins-and-writing-fragments-show-how-people-lived-in-the-western-desert/articleshow/132257013.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T13:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132257098,imgsize-162220.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDA